<l>ātaṉum pūtaṉuṅ kūṟiya viyalpoṭu</l>
<l>peyaroṟ ṟakaran tuvarak keṭumē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When proper names [ending in <foreign xml:lang="ta">-ṉ</foreign>] are followed by the</l>
<l>relationship term <foreign xml:lang="ta">tantai</foreign> ' father '.</l>
<l>the initial [consonant] therein disappears, the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">a</foreign> remains ;</l>
<l>that proper name, removing the consonant, loses the <foreign xml:lang="ta">aṉ.</foreign></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
